Ranger Help for: cooldowns
==========================

SUMMARY:
Ranger abilities use several different recovery timers. This keeps one
kind of work from blocking every other part of the guild.

TIMER TYPES:
  Combat      Attacks, combat defense, bow shots, and combat magic.
  Crafting    Making gear, arrows, traps, mixtures, and item prep.
  Fieldwork   Foraging, scouting, terrain study, hunting, and stealth.
  Travel      Running, trailblazing, guiding, locating, and messages.
  Companion   Attracting, calming, training, calling, and commanding.
  Camp        Camp stock, cooking, brewing, wards, and camp building.
  Recovery    Rest, meditation, ceremonies, Gaia's touch, and camp tend.

Recovery skills are stronger pauses. While recovering from one of those,
you need to wait before using another major Ranger ability.

EXAMPLES:
  A strike delays another combat maneuver, but not make arrow.
  Forage delays another fieldwork action, but not quickshot.
  Camp cook delays other camp work, but not attract.
  Rest and camp tend delay most Ranger abilities until recovery passes.

